# PKCERT Task 13: Advanced Model Evaluation & Handling Imbalanced Data

**Internship Project**

This project focuses on building and evaluating a classification model on the Telco Customer Churn dataset, with special emphasis on handling class imbalance using advanced techniques.

## Project Objectives
- Perform thorough data preprocessing and exploration
- Build a baseline classification model
- Evaluate using ROC-AUC and Learning Curves
- Handle imbalance using SMOTE and Class Weighting
- Provide comparative analysis and business recommendation

## Dataset
Telco Customer Churn (IBM) - Predict whether a customer will leave the telecom service.

## Key Techniques Used
- Logistic Regression
- ROC Curve & AUC
- Learning Curve Analysis
- SMOTE Oversampling
- Class Weighting
- Pipeline-based Preprocessing

## Results Summary
- Baseline ROC-AUC: 0.842
- Best approach for recall: SMOTE / Class Weighting

## Repository Contents
- Jupyter Notebook with full analysis
- Preprocessed data and models
- Visualizations (ROC, Learning Curve)

